! Timelord — Help

This plugin automatically records a revision every time you save a tiddler, and keeps it until you choose to prune it. No retention limit — storage is bounded only by the content you edit.

!! What gets captured

* ''Text and field edits.'' Any meaningful change — text, tags, type, custom fields — creates a revision. Saves that change nothing meaningful (e.g. only the ''modified'' timestamp) are skipped.
* ''Renames.'' Renaming a tiddler is recorded on the resulting revision, shown as ''renamed: Old → New''. The existing history stays attached.
* ''Deletions.'' Deleting a tiddler captures its final state as one last revision. The tiddler then appears in the ''Deleted Tiddlers'' sidebar tab, where you can restore it.

Revisions do ''not'' include system (`$:/`) or shadow tiddlers.

!! Reading timelord

Open any tiddler and expand the info panel (the ''i'' icon) — the ''Revisions'' tab lists every saved version, newest first.

Each entry shows:

* Revision number, timestamp, modifier, and character count.
* ''Restore this version'' — rolls the tiddler back. The current state is captured as a new revision first, so restore is undoable.
* ''Diff vs. current'' / ''Diff vs. previous'' — side-by-side text diff using TiddlyWiki's built-in diff widget.
* ''Fields: …'' — summary of non-text field changes. Click to expand before → after values. Tag changes render as green <code>+tag</code> / red <code>-tag</code>.

Long lists paginate at 20 entries with a ''Show all'' toggle; ''Oldest first'' reverses the sort.

!! Pausing capture

Use the ''Timelord Settings'' tab in the [[Control Panel|$:/ControlPanel]] to:

* ''Disable tracking'' globally — e.g. before a bulk import, then re-enable afterwards.
* Set an ''Exclusion Filter'' to skip specific tiddlers permanently (e.g. ''`[tag[NoTrack]]`'' skips everything tagged ''NoTrack'').

Saves that happen while tracking is paused or that match the exclude filter create no revision.

!! Pruning history

Infinite retention is the default. When you need to reclaim space or drop history intentionally:

* ''Per tiddler.'' In the Revisions tab, the ''Delete all history'' button removes every revision for the current tiddler (keeps the live tiddler). Useful if a tiddler accumulated unwanted history before you set an exclude filter.
* ''By filter.'' In the ''Timelord Stats'' tab, the ''Delete history matching filter'' action prunes history for every tiddler a filter matches. Useful for reclaiming storage across many tiddlers at once — confirmation is required because the blast radius is larger.

Deletion only removes revision tiddlers. The live tiddler is unaffected.

!! Storage and integrity

* The ''Timelord Stats'' tab shows total revisions, approximate storage, tiddlers with the most revisions, and any revisions flagged as broken.
* Revisions are stored as a mix of full snapshots and compact per-field deltas. A full snapshot is anchored every 10 revisions, so no chain ever grows unbounded between anchors.
* Under normal use, chains stay consistent. If sync conflicts or external edits damage them, the ''Timelord Settings'' tab has ''Verify'' and ''Repair'' actions that detect and isolate broken revisions.

